    ],
    "summary": "On 21 September 2023 at 0745 hours, production operators discovered an external leak on the production casing (B casing) of Well #98 on South Pass 28 13(V) jacket. Gas and oil were escaping through a hole in the side of the casing, creating a hydrocarbon sheen in Gulf waters. Despite immediately shutting in the well and closing the SCSSV, hydrocarbons continued to escape. Multiple intervention attempts were made over 8 days before a bridge plug was successfully set on 29 September, with the leak stopping on 30 September at 0132 hours. Total spill was estimated at 65.7 gallons of oil. The incident was attributed to equipment failure due to inadequate preventive maintenance and severe corrosion in an extremely harsh shallow saltwater environment.",
