    "additional_notes": "Incident involved multiple barrier failures due to inadequate maintenance in harsh environment. Production personnel demonstrated positive situational awareness by detecting the leak during routine field travel. However, organizational failures in maintenance programs and regulatory compliance (LOTO, equipment maintenance, access ladder) contributed significantly. Three INCs issued: E-100 for pollution, G-111 C for equipment maintenance failure, G-111 W for access ladder maintenance. Total estimated damage $260,723. Environmental impact: 65.7 gallons oil spilled, 4-mile sheen, no recovery due to sea conditions."
